  "source_text": "خْرى أَحْيَيْتَ مَنْ أَرَدْتَهُ بِجُودِكَ وَفَضْلِكَ، إِذًا أَشْكرُكَ وَأَحْمَدُكَ مِنْ قِبَلِ أَحِبَّتِكَ بِما أَحْيَيْتَهُمْ مِنَ الكَوْثَرِ الَّذِيْ جَرَى مِنْ فَمِ مَشِيَّتِكَ، يا إِلهِي لَمَّا أَحْيَيْتَهُمْ بِجُودِكَ فَأَثْبِتْهُمْ بِإِحْسانِكَ، لَمَّا أَدْخَلْتَهُمْ فِيْ سُرادِقِ أَمْرِكَ لا تَمْنَعْهُمْ بِفَضْلِكَ،",
  "translation": "I render Thee thanks, therefore, and extol Thee, in the name of all them that are dear to Thee, for that Thou hast caused them to be born again, by reason of the living waters which have flowed down out of the mouth of Thy will. Since Thou didst quicken them by Thy bounteousness, O my God, make them steadfastly inclined, through Thy graciousness, towards Thy will; and since Thou didst suffer them to enter into the Tabernacle of Thy Cause, grant by Thy grace that they may not be kept back from Thee.",
